text: Twenty students in a public health class at Dominican University will be trained in contact tracing this semester, according to Marin County health officials. After being trained, the students will potentially be able to conduct supervised contact tracing. https://t.co/9dBt4n0ZuE

text: The number of COVID-19 hospitalizations in San Francisco reached an all-time high of 101 on Monday, according to state data. In Alameda County, 10 more patients were hospitalized for a total of 198 as the county nears a record set last week. https://t.co/B89sNNjfgJ
